1.00	Angel_And_The_Bad_Man	Angel and the Badman	Angel and the Badman is a 1947 black-and-white Western film, starring John Wayne, Gail Russell, Harry Carey and Bruce Cabot which examines the ability of a gunman to renounce violence. This film, which was the first one Wayne produced as well as starred in, was a departure for this genre at the time it was released. The film was directed by James Edward Grant, Wayne's frequent screenwriting collaborator.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/c/c3/Angel_badman.jpg/220px-Angel_badman.jpg
